cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.MM

This paper deals with analyzing video data and extracting recurrent dynamics from it. The methodology combines ideas from nonlinear time series analysis and computational topology. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The use of topology in the methodology suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound) could also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with analyzing videos of vibrating vocal folds, which falls under the scope of cs.MM (Multimedia).
